                'slug' => 'company-registration-zambia-guide-2026',
                'excerpt' => 'A complete step-by-step guide to registering a company in Zambia, including legal requirements and costs.',
                'content' => '<p>Starting a business in Zambia is an exciting journey, but it requires navigating several regulatory steps. With the Zambian government\'s ongoing business reform initiatives, the process has become more streamlined than ever, yet understanding each step remains critical for a smooth registration experience. This comprehensive guide provides a clear roadmap for company registration in Zambia.</p><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507679799987-c73779587ccf?w=800&q=85" alt="Company registration Zambia guide" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:24px 0;" /><h2>Step 1: Company Name Reservation</h2><p>The first step is reserving your company name with the Patents and Companies Registration Agency (PACRA). You can check name availability online through the PACRA e-registry portal and reserve your preferred name. The reservation fee is approximately ZMW 150 and the name is reserved for 30 days. We recommend having 2\u20133 alternative names ready in case your first choice is unavailable.</p><h2>Step 2: Incorporation</h2><p>Submit your incorporation documents to PACRA, including:</p><ul><li><strong>Memorandum and Articles of Association:</strong> The constitutional documents of your company outlining its name, objectives, share structure, and governance rules</li><li><strong>Particulars of Directors and Shareholders:</strong> Full details including names, addresses, nationalities, and identification documents</li><li><strong>Registered Office Address:</strong> A physical address in Zambia for official correspondence</li><li><strong>Statement of Nominal Capital:</strong> Declaration of the company\'s share capital structure</li></ul><p>Incorporation typically takes 5\u201310 working days and costs approximately ZMW 2,500\u20135,000 depending on share capital and complexity.</p><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1450101499163-c8848c66ca85?w=800&q=85" alt="PACRA company registration" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:24px 0;" /><h2>Step 3: Tax Registration</h2><p>After incorporation, register with the Zambia Revenue Authority (ZRA) for:</p><ul><li><strong>Income Tax:</strong> Corporate income tax registration and Taxpayer Identification Number (TPIN)</li><li><strong>Value Added Tax (VAT):</strong> If your projected annual turnover exceeds ZMW 800,000</li><li><strong>PAYE:</strong> Pay-As-You-Earn registration if you will have employees</li><li><strong>Withholding Tax:</strong> For certain payments to suppliers and contractors</li></ul><h2>Step 4: Other Registrations</h2><p>Depending on your business type, additional registrations may be required, including NAPSA registration for employees, Workers\' Compensation Fund registration, sector-specific licenses (e.g., mining, tourism, financial services), and local council business permits.</p><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1664575602276-acd073f104c1?w=800&q=85" alt="Business registration process Zambia" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:24px 0;" /><p><a href="https://www.falanesolutions.com">Falane Solutions</a> provides end-to-end company registration services, guiding entrepreneurs through every step of the process. <a href="https://www.falanesolutions.com/contact">Contact our business registration team</a> to get started today.</p>',
                'tags' => json_encode(['company registration', 'Zambia', 'business setup', 'PACRA', 'entrepreneurship']),
                'category' => 'Business',
                'featured_image' => 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507679799987-c73779587ccf?w=1200&q=85',
                'is_published' => true,
                'published_at' => '2025-10-15 08:00:00',
